caption: My favorite place to order Chinese food! The portions are large and abundant, and the quality of the food here is always excellent. The delivery times if you order through their website is always fast! The favorites: salt and pepper eggplant, beef chow fun, xiao long bao (soup dumplings), scallion pancake, and the dry chili chicken!
Delicious food and amazing service! Thank you ML Kitchen! <3

Ordered searching for a good, somewhat close option for Asian food while I'm at work. Ordering online was easy, quick and gave a delivery time window. Ordered the Mongolian beef special and it was super good! Did normal spice and I know for next time to kick it up a bit higher but overall: great portions for the price and the taste is great.

Wonderful takeout experience from ML Kitchen! Their food is delicious — we had the lamb with cumin, hot boiled fish filet, dry chili chicken, and Japanese tofu with enoki mushroom. Because we ordered $40 worth, we also got a free chicken fried rice!! Really hit the spot and the food was ready for pickup in 15 minutes. We had a huge amount of leftovers. Well worth the money and we loved supporting a nearby local restaurant.
Excellent place for delicious chinese food. it was so appetizing. the service here is above par. the bill was appropriate for the quality.

A decent food option on a Sunday night when it seems every other restaurant in my neighborhood closes down.  ML Kitchen are great, but the pita and toppings are not as good as Liba Falafel truck.  At least it's cheaper.  I might try the dogmas and cinnamon baklava next time.

Best place for a vegan snack. OMG! So good. I always get the spicy pita snacker and its beyond delicious. They do gluten free bread too which is a definite plus in sf. Ooh and the fries on the snacker definitely seal the deal!

By far my favorite sushi place! The flavors are incredible and literally make your palette dance! The restaurant itself is quiet small but very nicely decorated. Only downside is the line outside starts before the restaurant opens so get there early!

While the food is average quality south western food, the prices for food and drinks were notably better than other restaurants on the strip. Use the ML Kitchen card and get one hour open bar. This was the only meal the five of us had(4drinks) that was less than $90 in Vegas over 3 days.
Food here is ok not really all that great, the mapa tofu is tue worse i ever had, the hot amd sour soup was so so, the soy sauce  chow mein was good

I want to give 5 stars but the only complaint I have is that it is extremely hot for my taste! My personal favorites are szechuan style chicken and orange chicken but I always have a hard time dealing with the heat from the red chillies in them. However, I still love it a lot and it is my favorite Chinese restaurant so far.

One of the best sushi spots around! Sat by the sushi bar and witnessed the magician sushi artists at work. Special thanks to Reka our amazing waitress! Moderate wait, but definitely worth it! Highly recommend - 10 stars!  Also, get the open invitation roll and/or the ramen. The tofu taste like pork! Actually, it tastes better!!

Update: Sesame chicken combo is just okay. Fried rice is biting and bland. Spicy wontons were also boring and mediocre. Soup dumplings (xiao long bao - XLB) we're just okay, not much soup.  ******************************************* Nicer atmosphere than your typical Chinese restaurant. I ordered salt and pepper shrimp (without shell) for takeout. It was underwhelming, not peppery enough. Also a bit pricey for what it was. I'll have to try something else for next time.

Hard to review the whole huge menu, but relative standard fair like Mongolian Beef, Sezchuan String Beans, Egg Foo young are very good.  Usually quite fast for take out orders (~15 min), good place, hope it can survive on take out until they can reopen for dine in

Found this place thanks to ML Kitchen.  What a great little place with a good variety of wildlife.  One of the few places where you can see a bald eagle up close and personal and a 2 toed sloth.  It's a very intimate place and the staff is very caring.  Definitely a good way to spend a couple of hours with the little ones.
I ordered from uber eat the first time. I had to go myself to ordered because it was so good. Will always go there for the dumplings. Food is great.

The overrated food truck. Went here based on the superb Google reviews and was not impressed. Maybe I was expecting my fish to sing "Under the sea" or tap dance for me given the reviews. I must admit the food was well cooked and the concept was solid. A good place to go if you want to try fish and chips for the first time. However, since Chicago is known for having amazing culinary options I would recommend trying something different

4 stars for food, -3 stars for service.  The waiter served with no smiles and didn’t even stop and look at you when he asks “so you want the check” or “boxes”. When I asked to complain to the restaurant owner, the waitress jumped out to defend the waiter and said, in her words, “you want the dish and we give you the dish, and you want the box then we give you the box. What else do you want?”. I swear when I asked to talk to the restaurant owner, I was smiling and didn’t yell or anything. The waiter and the waitress in the picture self defended so hard that they were accusing me for not talking to them but wanting to talk to the owner, and their attitude was pretty clear that they thought there’s absolutely nothing wrong with their attitude.  I’ve been here before so many times and I remember so clearly that they have one other staff that is so friendly and helpful. In the meantime, they have others that are so ignorant of what their job actually is and are with such bad attitude.  Again, 4 stars for food, and -3 for the bad services that the two waiter/waitress had towards me.  I’ve never left bad reviews like this on Google or Yelp. I also would never imagine the waiter/waitress would attack my inquiry to talk to the manager or restaurant owner and tell me that they are all very good waiter/waitress. I swear, again, that I was smiling and only making the request without any bad words. It’s very unfortunate that the waiter/waitress believes in what they did is correct.  Edit: just remembered one more thing the waitress said to me, as an evidence of how she understand doesn’t her job. I said “I’ve been here many time...” and her immediate response was “oh really? You’ve been here many times? Why don’t I remember ever seeing you?” Oh well...do I need to show you my credit bill? In any case, her response was very immature and not professional.
